                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="10500" author="krishnan_anantheswaran@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2004 08:23:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Junit test case that demonstrates the bug&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10501" author="krishnan_anantheswaran@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2004 08:25:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a valid use case for this. I want to be able to provide environment-independent defaults for runtime properties and only override the ones that actually differ on different environments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently I work around this by manually merging the properties defined in base v/s runtime. This is tedious.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10502" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2004 09:31:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, we should regard the defaults of a Properties instance here - I&apos;ve just adapted this. The reason why we lost the defaults up to now is that the given Properties were copied into a merged Properties instance via putAll, which of course doesn&apos;t copy the defaults.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10508" author="krishnan_anantheswaran@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 03:33:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Juergen,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wow! that was really quick.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see any updates to the CVS tree as a result of this fix. I assume you changed PropertyPlaceholderConfigurer.java and that I need to check out the CVS HEAD.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please advise.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards&lt;br/&gt;
Krishnan&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="10509" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 03:35:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, I discovered a side effect with PropertyOverrideConfigurer (which shares a common base class with PropertyPlaceholderConfigurer)afterwards, and haven&apos;t committed the change yet. I&apos;ll clarify this tonight; expect the change to be committed by tomorrow morning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
